# Verification Guide

## 1. Verify "Add New Project" Drawer
1.  Navigate to the **Mission Control** page.
2.  Click the **"Add New Project"** button.
3.  **Verify**: A drawer slides in from the right side.
4.  **Verify**: The drawer contains the "Name your project" input.
5.  Enter a project name and click **Next**.
6.  **Verify**: The drawer shows the "Select a git provider" options.
7.  Select a provider (e.g., GitHub).
8.  **Verify**: A new drawer (or modal content) appears for the connector.

## 2. Verify "Upload SBOM" Drawer
1.  Click the **"Upload SBOM File"** button.
2.  **Verify**: A drawer slides in from the right side.
3.  **Verify**: The drawer title is "Upload SBOM".
4.  Upload a file and follow the flow.

## 3. Verify "Project Details" Drawer
1.  Scroll down to the **Git Projects** list.
2.  Click on a project row (e.g., **"> Test Projects"**).
3.  **Verify**: A right-side drawer opens with the project name as the title.
4.  **Verify**: The drawer lists all repositories for that project.
5.  **Verify**: You can select repositories using the checkboxes.
6.  **Verify**: The "View Details" button for a repository works (or links correctly).
7.  **Verify**: Closing the drawer works.
